    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be severely restricted. As the moisture increases moist small and medium sized avalanches are possible. &lt;br/> The wind slabs can be released, especially at their margins, in particular on steep shady slopes. Weak layers in the old snowpack necessitate caution and restraint.</highlights>
      <comment>As a consequence of warming during the day, the likelihood of moist and wet avalanches being released will increase in particular on steep slopes below approximately 2600 m. &lt;br/> Dry avalanches can be released in deeper layers also.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The upper section of the snowpack is moist and its surface has a crust that is strong in many cases. &lt;br/> Precarious weak layers exist in the old snowpack especially on steep northwest, north and northeast facing slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
